<section>
    <h1 id="who-are-we">
        <a href="#who-are-we">Who are we?</a>
    </h1>
    <p>
        <strong>{dev.talk}</strong>
        is a free, community-driven meetup for software engineers and related disciplines in the south of the UK.
    </p>
    <p>
        The meetup was founded by
        <a href="https://blog.markoliver.website/Bio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mark Oliver</a>
        in 2024. He saw that Bournemouth was lacking a software engineering based meetup despite being a
        <a href="https://blog.markoliver.website/Bournemouth-Tech-Meetup-Rebirth" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tech Hub</a>
        on the South Coast of the UK, and as Wilton Knight once said
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=otzJszJ9MnA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">"one person can make a difference"</a>, so Mark decided to create the meetup, and the community around it.
    </p>
    <p>
        To stay focused on community commitment, {dev.talk} does not have sponsors.
        We do, however, have valued <a href="/supporters.html">supporters</a> who help with key practical needs such as
        <a href="/venues.html">venues</a> and videography so we can keep events free and community-led.
    </p>
    <p>
        Today, {dev.talk} continues to run because of the efforts of Mark and community volunteers who give their time to
        support speakers, film events, and help each meetup run smoothly.
    </p>
</section>
